narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Stronger skills in Japanese reading, writing, etc.
I learned to speak/read/write basic Japanese, as well as understand Japanese culture and communication.
I increased my speaking, writing, listening, and reading proficiency in Japanese.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I love this class, it's taught amazingly, the sensee's are fantastic, and it's a lot of fun.
This course had very good instructors, and the coursework/material were excellent. I really enjoyed the Japanese learning community.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! If you're interested in learning Japanese, there's no better way than studying it here.
I would highly recommend this course to anyone remotely interested in Japanese language or Japanese culture. It was one of the best decisions that I have made at Yale in terms of course selection.
